 - Scott Bates
<@U0265G76F>: <@U026PLK4S>  - this is likely opening a can of worms - but is there any interest for you guys in supplying @3x assets for vroom?
interest yes. Logistics - unknown.
BFF willingness to understand and fund 3x assets, unknown.
<@U0265G76F>: any sense of how long that would take? I'm not sure how many graphics we're talking about
I'm guessing willingness to understand and fund 3x assets is rather low....
think it'd take quite a bit actually - when you look at all the badges, animations, etc.
it'd be a rather large job
think everything is built to do it just fine, but totally rough guess — 40-60 hours
with a big caveat for how animation would need to be treated
yeah, with the way the maintenance conversation went, I'm guessing that's a nonstarter
<@U0289USNA>: do you suspect that things will look worse with this update? (similar to what happened when we updated lego?)
<@U02688JHZ> it should not be as evident as it was on lego because moat of the text is already live text in vroom.
To that point, <@U0265G76F> perhaps we just look at providing 3x for just the text
<@U0265G76F>: I looked through all the assets and there are less than 10 with text on them.  I can make a list and then see if somebody has time to just provide those couple.
No te olvides el español
señor correcta
